Key Match Events: Tim David hit a four off the last ball to seal victory
David Warner blew kisses at the crowd as he was booed off the pitch
Pre-Game Insights: Rachin Ravindra hit 68 runs off 35 balls to claim his first half-century in the format
Marsh finished with best bowling figures of 1-21
The three-match series is the last for both teams before the T20 World Cup in the United States and West Indies in June
Post-Match Reflections: Marsh said, 'I thought we were done, to be honest'
Warner said, 'We had a pretty good score, but we know they keep coming with the bat. The only way to stop them is to take wickets and we didn't really do that.'
Miscellaneous Highlights: Southee missed a catch off Josh Inglis
Phillips dropped Marsh next ball on the boundary
Adam Milne was smashed for 19 runs in the penultimate over
